com.interpss.core.acsc

Interface BaseAcscBus<TGen extends AcscGen,TLoad extends AcscLoad>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BaseAclfBus<TGen,TLoad>, Bus, com.hazelcast.nio.serialization.DataSerializable, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, ExtensionElement, IAclfBus, IAclfBusAdaptation, IAclfBusAdjustment, IAclfBusFunc, IAcscBus, IAdaptable, IBusSwitchBreakModel, NameTag, NetworkedElement, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AcscBus, BaseDStabBus<TGen,TLoad>, DStabBus, Dynamic3PBus, Steady3PBus
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AcscBusImpl, BaseAcscBusImpl, BaseDStabBusImpl, DStabBusImpl, Dynamic3PBusImpl, Steady3PBusImpl

    public interface BaseAcscBus<TGen extends AcscGen,TLoad extends AcscLoad>
extends BaseAclfBus<TGen,TLoad>, IAcscBus
    A representation of the model object 'Bus'. * Notes 1) for NotContribute bus, z1,z2=Zload, z0=Zload if grounded. * only SolidGround and Ungrounded allowd for groundType * * --- --- --- --- * | | | | * z1 z2 z0 z0 * | | | | * - - - * SolidG UnG * * 2) for Contributing bus, z1=x1, z2=x2, z0=x0+3*GX_R if grounded. * * --- --- --- --- * | | | | * E --z1--| z2 z0+3*GX_R z0 z0 * | | | | * - - - * ZG SolidG UnG * * E could be 1.0/0deg or use LF voltage to calculate AcscBus could be extended using IAascBus interface

    The following features are supported:

    • Sc Code
    • Seq Data Initialized
    • Pos Seq Data Initialized
    • Neg Seq Data Initialized
    • Zero Seq Data Initialized
    • Sc Gen Z1
    • Sc Gen Z2
    • Sc Gen Z0
    • Sc Load Shunt Y1
    • Sc Load Shunt Y2
    • Sc Load Shunt Y0
    • Three Seq Voltage
    • Sc Fixed Shunt Y0
    • Sc Switched Shunt Y0
    • Equiv Z1
    • Equiv Z2
    • Equiv Z0
    • Grounding
    See Also:
    AcscPackage.getBaseAcscBus()
